---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy - vibereport"
  description="How vibereport handles your data."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-12 pb-16">
    <a
      href="/"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-xs text-tokyo-dimmed hover:text-tokyo-text transition-colors mb-8"
    >
      &larr; Back to home
    </a>

    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-tokyo-text mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-sm text-tokyo-dimmed leading-relaxed">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-tokyo-text mb-2">What we collect</h2>
        <p>
          vibereport analyzes <strong class="text-tokyo-text">commit messages only</strong>.
          We never read, store, or transmit your source code. The CLI parses your local git history
          and extracts metadata: commit counts, author trailers, timestamps, and language statistics
          from file extensions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-tokyo-text mb-2">Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          By default, scan results are uploaded to vibereport.dev so they appear on the
          community leaderboard. You can opt out with <code class="text-tokyo-cyan">--no-share</code>.
          Shared reports include: repository name, AI ratio, vibe score, grade, roast, language breakdown,
          and commit counts. No source code, diffs, or file contents are ever sent.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-tokyo-text mb-2">Web scans</h2>
        <p>
          When you scan a repo via the website, we fetch commit data from the GitHub API.
          Results are cached for 10 minutes per repository. The same metadata is stored as CLI scans.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-tokyo-text mb-2">Storage</h2>
        <p>
          Reports are stored in Cloudflare D1 (SQLite). We use Cloudflare Workers for the API
          and Vercel for the frontend. No third-party data brokers or ad networks.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-tokyo-text mb-2">Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          We use Vercel Analytics for basic page view metrics. No cookies, no cross-site tracking,
          no personal data collection.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-tokyo-text mb-2">Data deletion</h2>
        <p>
          Want your report removed? Open an issue on
          <a
            href="https://github.com/monkeycs60/vibereport/issues"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-tokyo-cyan hover:text-tokyo-cyan/80 transition-colors"
          >GitHub</a> with the repository name and we'll delete it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-tokyo-text mb-2">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions? Open an issue on
          <a
            href="https://github.com/monkeycs60/vibereport"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-tokyo-cyan hover:text-tokyo-cyan/80 transition-colors"
          >GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
